The paper deals with decision problems related to pushdown vector addition systems, which are a combination of pushdown automata and vector addition systems. This involves concepts from formal languages (pushdown automata), formal logic (boundedness), and discrete structures (vector addition systems). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves the study of reachability sets, which is a topic in computational complexity and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The use of pushdown automata and grammar-controlled vector addition systems also suggests cs.PL (Programming Languages) as a possible sub-category. The paper also involves formal languages and automata theory, which are topics in cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of derivation trees, which is a topic in cs.SC (Symbolic Computation).
